members.name: creditPool
members.doc: Settings that control the behavior of the credit pool. If this value is left empty, then the entitlement is unlimited and resources should not have prices

members.name: policies
members.doc: Defines the behavior of the entitlement. Default policy for all resources, but may be overridden by a specific resource

members.name: resources
members.doc: A set of resources that share the credit pool and policies of the entitlement

members.name: fromHour
members.doc: Hour that this interval starts from. If this is set then to_hour must also be set

members.name: fromMinute
members.doc: Minute that this interval starts from. If this is set then to_minute must also be set

members.name: fromWeekDay
members.doc: Weekday that this interval starts from. If this is set then to_week_day must also be set

members.name: toHour
members.doc: Hour that this interval ends at. If this is set then from_hour must also be set

members.name: toMinute
members.doc: Minute that this interval ends at. If this is set then from_minute must also be set

members.name: toWeekDay
members.doc: Weekday that this interval ends at. If this is set then from_week_day must also be set

members.doc: Flag that indicates the server failed to calculate the `total` field.

members.doc: Total number of items that match the query. Returned if offset paging is used and the `tooManyToCount` flag is not set.

members.name: cursorPaging
members.doc: Cursor token pointing to a page of results. Not used in the first request. Following requests use the cursor token and not `filter` or `sort`.

members.name: fields
members.doc: Array of projected fields. A list of specific field names to return. If `fieldsets` are also specified, the union of `fieldsets` and `fields` is returned.

members.name: fieldsets
members.doc: Array of named, predefined sets of projected fields. A array of predefined named sets of fields to be returned. Specifying multiple `fieldsets` will return the union of fields from all sets. If `fields` are also specified, the union of `fieldsets` and `fields` is returned.
